00:52:00.910 --> 00:52:04.550
But if you then analyze
all the possible diagrams,

00:52:04.550 --> 00:52:09.530
you will actually figure out
that they can-- no matter

00:52:09.530 --> 00:52:13.030
what you do, what permutation
of photons and atoms you

00:52:13.030 --> 00:52:16.470
have-- the fourth order
diagrams will be such

00:52:16.470 --> 00:52:19.190
that they are
always distinguished

00:52:19.190 --> 00:52:23.630
by in this intermediate
zone, whether you have

00:52:23.630 --> 00:52:27.270
two atomic excitations
or photonic excitations.

00:52:27.270 --> 00:52:30.430
And so what I do for you
were the two diagrams,

00:52:30.430 --> 00:52:37.590
which are representative for a
whole class of diagrams here.

00:52:37.590 --> 00:52:40.311
But absolutely,
